{
  "text": "In another study, Lew/SSN rats were fed with different ratios of EPA and DHA before the induction of streptococcal cell wall (SCW) arthritis. EPA and DHA could reduce the severity of arthritis symptoms, but synovial histopathological findings seemed to improve more with EPA than with DHA [CITATION_1] .",
